title: Test
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Unemployment rate, with a total of 21 data points.
Overall Unemployment rate has decreased over the Year
Unemployment rate is roughly constant from 1999 to 2000, gradually decreasing from 2000 to 2001, and lastly gradually constant from 2001 to 2019.
The steepest decrease occurs in between the Year 2000 and 2001.
Max Unemployment rate about 2.55 was recorded at Year 1999
Min Unemployment rate about 1.02 was recorded at Year 2019
This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Unemployment rate, with a total of 21 data points. The chart has 3 significant trends.
The longest trend is slightly decreasing which exists from 1999 to 2010.
Conversely, the next significant trend is moderately decreasing which exists from 2013 to 2019.
Differently, the next significant trend is extremely decreasing which exists from 2010 to 2013.
